attributes.review: Unfortunately while embarking on this nuisance of a code sequence, I remembered that I should not have high expectations for the functionality considering the fact that it’s “#1 in news.” With that being said, I was just as disappointed after I downloaded than when I was when I found out this thing even existed. Like for example, why would I download an app that only consists of information of rapists and tax fraud when I’m obviously looking for UNBIASED (it shouldn’t even have to be clarified) real information. Also, I would like to add that there is no reason to market off of votes if you know that your positions/views can cater to the people you’re actually serving; the policies should be such a no brainer that these strenuous efforts are concerning. I have never seen anyone in my life go to such lengths to brainwash/profit off of ignorant, sorry, oblivious people. Even I, during my student election drew the line at homemade individual personalized cupcakes so that people knew i knew them. So, this is weird to me.

I was utterly disgusted. I screamed and threw my cellular device across the room. It landed with a resounding crunch. I picked it up and saw the screen had tiny vein-like cracks spiderwebbing over the entire thing. I’m very disappointed with this app. I’d heard the man in the Oval Office was a molester of some sort. This was just far TOO much. I’m currently shaking as I’m writing this review. So much so, that my finger has multiple microscopic glass shards in it due to my shattered screen, earlier caused by this atrocious app. DO NOT DOWNLOAD IT!!

when opening the app i thought my phone was tweaking!!! i had never seen such a creature before! it was an orange man and i thought “this just can’t be my president, i think the app was hacked.” but now looking up who our president was (since he’s been hiding in a bunker 99.9999% of his time in office and i didn’t know who he was)  i saw that that was our president and i could not believe it 😭😭😭😭🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢😹. so sorry to leave a bad review but it’s all the truth. #jkimnotsorry
